      "content": "bro that is literally the same 2D array you just said wouldn't work lol. a 10000x10000 array of integers in python is gonna be like several hundred MBs at least. the judge is definitely gonna kill that with MLE.\n\nu gotta actually fix the memory usage. can u do it with just one or two rows? or use some other trick to keep the footprint low? i just need the code to pass the limits so i can move on.",
